---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Léo Camuzard - CV</title>
  <script src="/script.js" defer></script>
  <script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/alpinejs@3.x.x/dist/cdn.min.js"></script>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body x-data="{ skill: null, descriptions1: {
  'Kubernetes & Docker': 'I have worked closely with Docker and Kubernetes for the past 6 years. My experience includes managing EKS clusters, writing Helm charts, writing custom Operators, and deploying containerized applications.',
  'GitOps (ArgoCD)': 'Over the past 3 years, I have designed GitOps workflows using ArgoCD, including the development of custom ArgoCD plugins in Python to extend its capabilities.',
  'Programming (Python, Go)': 'I have written and maintained complex Python applications for 9 years, using OOP, pyproject.toml, testing frameworks, and functional design. My Go experience focuses on developing Kubernetes controllers and building web APIs with Swagger documentation.',
  'CI/CD Pipelines': 'I have built and maintained pipelines with Jenkins (Groovy), ArgoCD, and GitHub Actions, enabling reliable and automated delivery.',
  'Cloud Infrastructure (AWS)': 'For the past 6 years, I have deployed scalable, production-grade infrastructure in AWS, including networking, compute, storage, and IAM components.',
  'Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)': 'I have been using Terraform for 6 years to manage platform infrastructure, primarily targeting AWS with reusable, modular configurations.'
} }" class="font-sans bg-gray-50 text-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 transition-colors duration-500 overflow-x-hidden">
  <div class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-6 py-12">
    <button id="darkModeButton" class="fixed top-4 right-4 z-50 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 via-pink-500 to-red-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full shadow-lg hover:opacity-90 transition-all">
      Dark Mode
    </button>

    <div id="mainContent" class="parallax w-full max-w-4xl p-8 rounded-3xl shadow-glass backdrop-blur-md bg-white/10 dark:bg-white/5 border border-white/20">
      <header class="text-center mb-12 fade-up">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-hero-gradient">Léo Camuzard</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-secondary mt-2"><b>Senior DevOps Engineer</b></p>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-10 fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4 border-b border-primary pb-2">About Me</h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          A passionate Senior DevOps engineer specializing in Kubernetes, automation, and cloud infrastructure. Enthusiastic about GitOps workflows and Kubernetes controller development.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10 fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4 border-b border-primary pb-2">Experience</h2>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-primary">Senior DevOps Engineer – OpenBet, London</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary mt-3"><b>2021 – now</b></p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-5">• Led the design and operation of <b>EKS</b>-based Kubernetes clusters, including networking with <b>Cilium</b>, autoscaling, RBAC, <b>Kyverno</b> policies, and upgrade strategies.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Built and maintained <b>Infrastructure-as-Code</b> with <b>Terraform</b> for <b>AWS</b> services like: EKS, EC2, VPC, RDS, S3, IAM, Route 53, SNS, and ECR.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Developed and maintained <b>Kubernetes Operators</b> in <b>Go</b> to automate infrastructure and application lifecycle tasks.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Implemented <b>GitOps</b> workflows using <b>ArgoCD</b>, reducing deployment errors and increasing release reliability.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Supported system observability using <b>Prometheus</b>, <b>Grafana</b>, and <b>Alertmanager</b>; involved in on-call rotations and incident response.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Created internal automation tooling in <b>Python</b> to support platform and developer operations.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Collaborated closely with backend and product teams to support feature rollout, infrastructure performance tuning, and reliability improvements.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Supported developers by containerizing applications, authoring <b>Helm</b> charts, and integrating with our internal image registry (<b>Harbor</b>).</p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-primary mt-8">DevOps Engineer – Light & Wonder, London</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary mt-3"><b>2018 – 2021</b></p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-5">• Designed and maintained complex infrastructures with <b>Terraform</b>, in <b>AWS</b>, <b>VMware</b> / NSX, managing hundreds of instances across dev, staging, and production.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Implemented <b>CI/CD</b> pipelines with Groovy Libraries for <b>Jenkins</b>.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Developed automation tools in <b>Python</b> using OOP, pyproject.toml, unittests, functional testing.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Managed EKS clusters with <b>Terraform</b> and <b>Helm</b>.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Strengthened platform security by integrating <b>Vault</b>, SELinux and encrypted connections.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Configured and maintained Centos servers for AWS and VMware to run applications such as webapps (Apache, Nginx), databases (Informix, PostgreSQL), Java applications.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Helped developers to deploy their applications with <b>Ansible</b>.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Adopted SAFe with Scrum to increase delivery predictability and alignment across teams.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Participated in the 24/7 on-call rotation for incident response in production environments.</p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-primary mt-8">Software Integrator - CGI, Paris</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary mt-3"><b>2015 – 2018</b></p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-5">I did a three year apprenticeship as a software integrator for CGI. My main tasks were:</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Automation of the environment deployments with <b>Jenkins, Ansible, Docker, Shell scripting, Gitlab</b>.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Deployment and maintenance of hundreds of environments for integration and acceptance with <b>Redhat 7, Weblogic/Embedded, Oracle, eldap, Batch</b>.</p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">• Support for different technical teams.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10 fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4 border-b border-primary pb-2">Skills</h2>
        <ul class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-lg">
          <template x-for="label in Object.keys(descriptions1)" :key="label">
            <li
              @click="skill = label"
              class="flex items-center justify-center text-center bg-amber-100 dark:bg-white/10 p-4 rounded-xl hover:scale-105 transition-transform cursor-pointer"
              x-text="label"
            ></li>
          </template>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-10 fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4 border-b border-primary pb-2">Education</h2>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-medium text-primary">Master's Degree in Computer Science, Paris</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary"><b>ESGI, 2018</b></p>
          <p class="text-lg mt-2">Specialized in Network, Systems, and Cloud Computing. Completed a 3-year apprenticeship while studying.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="text-center fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4 border-b border-primary pb-2">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-lg">Email: <a href="mailto:leo@example.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">leo.camuzard@gmail.com</a></p>
        <p class="text-lg">LinkedIn: <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/camuzard" class="text-primary hover:underline">linkedin.com/in/camuzard</a></p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Skill Modal outside scrollable content -->
  <template x-if="skill">
    <div class="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 flex items-center justify-center z-50">
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-black dark:text-white rounded-xl p-6 w-full max-w-md mx-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2" x-text="skill"></h3>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4" x-text="descriptions1[skill]"></p>
        <button @click="skill = null" class="text-primary hover:underline text-sm">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </template>
</body>